---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-prose.njk",
  "permalink": "/pricing/",
  "slug": "pricing",
  "bodyClass": "page--bofu",
  "sec": {
    "aiH": "TechBrot pricing, in five questions.",
    "faqH": "Questions about cost."
  },
  "title": "Fixed-Fee Bookkeeping & QuickBooks Pricing · TechBrot",
  "description": "Real fixed-fee ranges for bookkeeping, QuickBooks cleanup, setup, migration, payroll & CFO. Written scope, no hourly billing. Call (877) 751-5575.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Pricing" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "Pricing · Fixed-fee, written scope",
    "heading": "Fixed-fee pricing. Written scope before any work.",
    "subheading": "Most firms hide pricing and bill by the hour. TechBrot does the opposite: every engagement is a fixed fee against a written scope, agreed before work begins. Here are the real ranges across every service &mdash; your exact fixed fee is quoted in writing within 3 business days of a free discovery call.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=pricing", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Explore Services", "href": "/accounting/services/", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>Always:</strong> fixed-fee &middot; written scope before work begins &middot; no hourly billing &middot; free 30-minute discovery call &middot; written quote within 3 business days &middot; no long-term lock-in on recurring engagements.",
    "source": "TechBrot Inc. &middot; independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Start here",
    "heading": "Get your exact fixed fee.",
    "lede": "A free 30-minute discovery call, then a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days &mdash; the exact number, in writing, before you commit to anything. No hourly billing, no obligation.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=pricing", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

{#- ═══ F2 PRICING (BASELINE, canonical Sheet-0 figures). t-bofu→t-prose. Every
    baseline heading verbatim; canonical figures EXACT (tldr text + `pricing` data
    table, untouched). #pricing-tldr-body speakable preserved; #pricing-in-brief-text
    rendered by the layout TL;DR. ai-summary + faq rendered by t-prose (sec.aiH/faqH). ═══ -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="pricing-credentials">
  <div class="ct">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-bottom:14px;"><span class="rule-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span></span><span></span></span>Verifiable Intuit credentials</p>
    {% include "partials/intuit-badges.njk" %}
  </div>
</section>

{#- TL;DR (body) — canonical figures verbatim. #pricing-tldr-body = speakable. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="pricing-tldr" style="padding-top:8px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">How TechBrot pricing works.</h2>
    <div class="tldr-prose"><p id="pricing-tldr-body">Every TechBrot engagement is fixed-fee with a written scope agreed before any work begins &mdash; no hourly billing. Real ranges: <strong>monthly bookkeeping $400&ndash;$2,500+/month</strong>, cleanup $1,500&ndash;$15,000+, catch-up $2,000&ndash;$20,000+, QuickBooks setup $750&ndash;$5,000+, migration $2,500&ndash;$10,000+, payroll $150&ndash;$800+/month, sales tax compliance $250&ndash;$1,500+/month, and fractional CFO $3,000&ndash;$8,000+/month (by application). Where you land depends on real factors &mdash; transaction volume, number of accounts and entities, history depth, file complexity. The 30-minute discovery call is free; your exact fixed fee is delivered in writing within 3 business days. No long-term lock-in on recurring engagements. Tax filing isn&rsquo;t included (your CPA handles that), but a year-end CPA handoff is included free.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- PATH — 4 steps (additive, not baseline) → process-grid. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="pricing-path">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">From question to fixed fee</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:22px;">Four steps to a number in writing.</h2>
    <div class="process-grid">
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">STEP 1</div><h3>Free discovery call</h3><p>30 min &middot; no obligation</p></div>
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">STEP 2</div><h3>Written scope</h3><p>within 3 business days</p></div>
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">STEP 3</div><h3>Fixed fee, in writing</h3><p>no hourly billing</p></div>
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n process-step__n--done">STEP 4 &check;</div><h3>Work begins</h3><p>named operator</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- SHAPES — 3 engagement shapes (baseline h3s: Monthly retainer / Fixed-fee project / Senior retainer). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="pricing-shapes" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Engagement shapes</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Every engagement fits one of three shapes.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:68ch;">However the work is priced, it takes one of three forms &mdash; so you know what you&rsquo;re committing to before the discovery call.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in shapes %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ s.label }}</span><h3>{{ s.name }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:8px 0 0;"><strong>For:</strong> {{ s.forList | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- THE FULL TABLE — canonical Sheet-0 ranges from `pricing` data (untouched). vs-table→.cmp. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="pricing-table">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The full table</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Every service, every range.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">Canonical fixed-fee ranges, identical everywhere on the site. All engagements: fixed fee, written scope before work begins, no hourly billing.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">TechBrot fixed-fee pricing across all engagement types.</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Service</th><th scope="col">Engagement type</th><th scope="col">Fee range</th><th scope="col">Cadence</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for row in pricing %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" data-col="Service"><a href="{{ row.href }}?intent={{ row.intent }}">{{ row.service }}</a></th>
          <td data-col="Engagement type" style="color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ row.type | safe }}</td>
          <td class="num us" data-col="Fee range"><strong>{{ row.range | safe }}</strong>{% if row.unit %}<span style="color:var(--color-ink-faint);font-weight:400;">{{ row.unit }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
          <td data-col="Cadence" style="color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ row.cadence | safe }}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="prose" style="font-size:13.5px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:14px;">Sales tax compliance also carries a one-time nexus review of $500&ndash;$3,000. Your specific quote follows the free discovery call within 3 business days.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- BY SERVICE — links to the 5 sub-pages (additive heading). -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="pricing-by-service">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Pricing in detail</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Detailed pricing, by service.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">The full price grain for each major engagement &mdash; the tiers, what drives the figure, and what&rsquo;s included &mdash; on its own page.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for card in byService %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ card.href }}?intent=pricing"><h3>{{ card.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ card.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">See the detail <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- WHY FIXED-FEE — prose. -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="pricing-why" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Why fixed-fee</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Why we don&rsquo;t bill by the hour.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Hourly billing has a structural problem: it penalizes you for the provider&rsquo;s inefficiency. The slower they work, the more you pay. The invoice is unpredictable, and you can&rsquo;t budget around it. Worse, it makes you hesitate to call your own accountant &mdash; because every question starts a meter.</p>
      <p>TechBrot prices every engagement as a fixed fee against a written scope. You know the total cost before any work begins. Call as often as you need within the engagement &mdash; no meter. If the work genuinely expands beyond the agreed scope, the fee is re-quoted and re-approved in writing before anything proceeds. <strong>You are never surprised by an invoice.</strong></p>
      <p>This only works because the work is delivered by Certified ProAdvisors efficient enough to price confidently. The fixed fee is a statement of competence: we know how long good work takes, so we can quote it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- INCLUDES — 6 (baseline h3s). -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="pricing-includes">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Every engagement</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Every fixed fee includes these.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:66ch;">Six things in every engagement, whatever the service or the number.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for inc in includes %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ inc.name }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ inc.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- STANDARDS — prose + trust-row. -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="pricing-standards" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Pricing standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Pricing maintained by the TechBrot platform team.</h2>
    <div class="prose read--doc">
      <p>Pricing on this page is maintained by the <strong>Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</strong> at TechBrot Inc., a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm. Ranges reflect current operational pricing and are reviewed quarterly. Specific fixed fees are quoted per engagement after a free discovery call. Where pricing changes, this page and the individual service pages are updated together to stay consistent.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row" style="margin-top:22px;">
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Entity</p><p class="trust-row__label">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Delaware C-Corp &middot; independent ProAdvisor firm</p></div>
      <div class="trust-row__divider"></div>
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Model</p><p class="trust-row__label">Fixed-fee &middot; written scope before work &middot; no hourly billing</p></div>
      <div class="trust-row__divider"></div>
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Certifications</p><p class="trust-row__label">Active Intuit ProAdvisor &mdash; QBO L2, Desktop, Enterprise, Payroll, Bookkeeping</p></div>
      <div class="trust-row__divider"></div>
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">Independence</p><p class="trust-row__label">Not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p></div>
    </div>
    <p class="prose" style="font-size:13.5px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:14px;">Pricing last reviewed: May 2026.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- NEXT — 4 route cards (baseline h3s: Service Catalog / Which Service Do I Need? / Why Trust TechBrot / Get a Quote). -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="pricing-next">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Next steps</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">Where to go next.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for card in nextCards %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ card.href }}"><h3>{{ card.name }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ card.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ card.cta }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
